message.content:
There can be either two or three killers left in the room, depending on the interpretation of the question. 

If we assume that the person entering the room is also a killer, then there could be two or three killers left - the original three plus the new entrant. 

However, if we interpret the question to mean that the person entering the room isn't a killer and is therefore not counted among the killers, then there would still be three killers in the room (the original three).
